<h3>
    The Medical Bill has the least overall debt balance.  Your goal is to get rid of that debt as soon as possible.  While making the minimum payments on the Car Loan and the Student Loan,
    you will also make EXTRA payments on the Medical Bill.  Your extra payment may only be $5 over the minimum amount, that's ok.  Pay as much as you can in extra based on your income.
    Once the Medical Bill is paid off, roll the $294.49 (plus your extra payment) into a new extra payment on the Car Loan!
</h3>

<h3>The Snowball methood seems slow to start.  Once the first account has been paid down, watch how quickly the next, and the next will be paid off!  </h3>

